Dear Chairman Geddes & Committee Members,

I am writing to formally request that the Committee include an item under
the *Superintendent=E2=80=99s Report* at the next regular committee meeting=
 to
review and explain *DESE-reported student restraint trends for Attleboro
Public Schools across multiple years (2016=E2=80=9317 through 2024=E2=80=93=
25)*. This would
also require the attendance of the Special Educator Director to speak to
some of the specifics.

I have attached *all relevant DESE Student Restraint Report spreadsheets*
covering these years for the Committee=E2=80=99s reference. I have also att=
ached a
reference document, *including my* *preliminary findings, as well as 25
suggested questions to the administration.*
------------------------------
*Why this warrants agenda time*

Across multiple years, *Attleboro elementary schools appear as statewide
outliers* by total restraints and/or restraint rate per 100 enrolled
students. Importantly, the *outlier building changes over time*, which
suggests district-level operational factors rather than a single isolated
issue.

This is not a request to compare schools for evaluative purposes. It is a
request for *public explanation and contextualization of year-over-year
trends*, particularly where the data show sharp increases (=E2=80=9Cspikes=
=E2=80=9D)
followed by declines.
------------------------------
*Key data highlights (from attached DESE reports)*
***please see attached overview for more in depth analysis***
*2024=E2=80=9325 (most recent year)*

   - *A. Irvin Studley Elementary*
      - *212 total restraints*
      - *19 students restrained*
      - *Rate: 56.99 restraints per 100 enrolled*
      - *Statewide rank: #6 by total restraints and #6 by rate*
      - *9 reported injuries*
   - Statewide context (schools with visible data):
      - *Median rate:* 6.44 per 100
      - *95th percentile rate:* 53.48 per 100
      =E2=86=92 Studley=E2=80=99s rate exceeds the 95th percentile.

*Prior spike years*

   - *2022=E2=80=9323: Peter Thacher Elementary*
      - *116 total restraints*
      - *Rate: 26.24 per 100*
      - *Statewide rank: #5 by total restraints*
   - *2023=E2=80=9324: Hill-Roberts Elementary*
      - *99 total restraints*
      - *Rate: 23.68 per 100*
      - *Statewide rank: #10 by total restraints*

------------------------------
*Notable year-to-year shifts*

The data also show *large single-year changes* that warrant explanation:

   - *Studley:* 82 (2023=E2=80=9324) =E2=86=92 *212 (2024=E2=80=9325)*
   - *Hill-Roberts:* 17 (2022=E2=80=9323) =E2=86=92 *99 (2023=E2=80=9324)* =
=E2=86=92 30 (2024=E2=80=9325)
   - *Thacher:* 35 (2021=E2=80=9322) =E2=86=92 *116 (2022=E2=80=9323)* =E2=
=86=92 52 (2023=E2=80=9324)

In addition, some peak years show *high =E2=80=9Crepeat restraint intensity=
=E2=80=9D*,
meaning many restraints concentrated among a small number of students (for
example, *~11 restraints per restrained student at Studley in 2024=E2=80=93=
25*).
------------------------------
*Information requested during the Superintendent=E2=80=99s Report*

I am asking for a *fact-based explanation on the public record*, including:

   - What operational or staffing changes occurred in the years preceding
   or during these spikes
   - Whether there were program relocations, staffing transitions, or
   policy/practice changes between buildings
   - How injury reporting is defined and documented for DESE reporting
   - What steps were taken following spike years to reduce restraint
   frequency and repetition

------------------------------
*Public comment notice*

I intend to speak during *public comment* regarding how this information
has been handled and discussed by the Committee to date. My goal is
transparency, clarity, and ensuring the public understands both the data
and the district=E2=80=99s response to it. I look forward to hearing though=
tful
questions from each committee member.

Thank you for your time and for considering this agenda request. Please let
me know if the Committee would like any more information.

Respectfully,
*Joey Ford*

